          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Thin self-supporting carbon foils, approximate surface",
                "density 20 mug/cm**2, were used in energy range 2.80-",
                "4.745 MeV. At energies above 4.745 MeV using a gas",
                "target which removed systematic errors associated with",
                "foil buckling, foil positioning and beam shifts that",
                "are inherent in the use of the foil targets."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "THEO"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".Phase-shift analysis."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-  By author.  Absolute cross section measurements were",
                "performed using a gas target.  The absolute cross",
                "section measured at 90 degree with 6.510 MeV beam",
                "energy and the excitation functions, were used to",
                "assign absolute differential cross sections in all the",
                "angular distributions."
              ]
            }
          ],
